        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <h3>Does Fieldwire integrate with Procore?</h3>
        <p>Yes, there is a Procore integration that allows syncing plans and tasks between the platforms. Some GCs use both: Procore for project management and financials, Fieldwire for field team usability.</p>

        <h3>Is Fieldwire good for small construction companies?</h3>
        <p>The free plan is great for small companies with basic needs. Paid plans get expensive per-user for small teams. If you have fewer than 5 people and need both field tools and financial management, a full platform like Contractor Foreman ($49/mo for the whole team) may be better value.</p>

        <h3>What happened to Fieldwire after Hilti acquired it?</h3>
        <p>Fieldwire continued operating as a standalone product post-acquisition. Hilti has maintained the platform without forcing an enterprise-only pricing model. The product has continued to improve, with BIM support and analytics features added after the acquisition.</p>

